-- Insurer Lancashire names new CEO after founder Brindle retires
-- By Richa Naidu in Bangalore
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 02:39AM EDT
-- None



April 16 (Reuters) - Lancashire Holdings <LRE.L> said head underwriting officer Alex Maloney would take the helm as its chief executive after the property and casualty insurer announced the retirement of founder Richard Brindle.

Brindle, the company's chief executive since he started Lancashire in 2005, will be stepping down on April 30.